Full release notes: https://github.com/jullienl/HPE-COM-PowerShell-Library/releases/tag/v1.0.23



38 x NEW CMDLETS

Save-HPEGLSession / Restore-HPEGLSession
Save and restore workspace sessions for multi-workspace automation without re-authenticating. Automatic token refresh on restore.

Invoke-HPECOMExternalServiceVCenterFirmwareBaselineSync
Trigger a firmware baseline sync job for a VMware vCenter external service. Supports -Async and -ScheduleTime/-Interval.

Confirm-HPEGLLocation
Revalidate expired locations and reset the validation cycle to 6, 12 (default), or 18 months.

Restart-HPECOMAppliance
Trigger an OS reboot of an HPE Secure Gateway appliance. Supports -Async.

Add-HPECOMApprovalPolicyToGroup / Remove-HPECOMApprovalPolicyFromGroup
Attach or detach an approval policy from a group.

Get-HPECOMApprovalRequest
Retrieve pending or historical job approval requests. Filter by state (PENDING, APPROVED, DECLINED).

Resolve-HPECOMApprovalRequest
Approve or decline a pending job approval request. Supports optional -Remarks.

Get-HPECOMOneViewServerProfileTemplate
Retrieve server profile templates from OneView appliances registered in COM. Supports -ApplianceName and -ShowAttributes.

New-HPECOMSettingOneViewAppliance / Set-HPECOMSettingOneViewAppliance
Create and update OneView VM appliance settings (22 parameters across 8 categories).

New-HPECOMSettingOneViewSynergyAppliance / Set-HPECOMSettingOneViewSynergyAppliance
Create and update Synergy Composer appliance settings.

New-HPECOMSettingOneViewServerProfileTemplate / Set-HPECOMSettingOneViewServerProfileTemplate
Capture a server profile template from a OneView appliance and manage it as a COM setting.

New-HPECOMSettingOneViewApplianceSoftware / Set-HPECOMSettingOneViewApplianceSoftware
Define the target OneView firmware version for managed OVE appliances.

Add-HPECOMApplianceToGroup / Remove-HPECOMApplianceFromGroup
Manage OVE appliance group membership. Use -All on Remove- to clear all members.

Update-HPECOMGroupApplianceFirmware
Trigger firmware updates for all appliances in an OVE group. Supports -Force and -Wait.

Invoke-HPECOMGroupApplianceSettings
Apply the OneView appliance settings assigned to a group to all member appliances. Supports -Async.

Copy-HPECOMGroupApplianceServerProfileTemplate
Push server profile templates from the group''s template setting to all member appliances. Supports -Async.

Invoke-HPECOMApplianceRefreshSettings
Pull the latest configuration from a OneView appliance into COM. Supports -Async, -ScheduleTime, -Interval.

Set-HPECOMServerUIDIndicator
Turn the server UID indicator light on or off to physically locate a server in the data center.

Get-HPEGLWebhook / New-HPEGLWebhook / Set-HPEGLWebhook / Send-HPEGLWebhookTest / Remove-HPEGLWebhook / Confirm-HPEGLWebhookEndpoint / Invoke-HPEGLWebhookDeliveryRetry
Full lifecycle management for HPE GreenLake platform webhook endpoints including delivery retry and endpoint verification.

Get-HPEGLWebhookSubscription / Add-HPEGLWebhookSubscription / Remove-HPEGLWebhookSubscription
Manage event type subscriptions linking HPE GreenLake event types to webhook endpoints. Supports OData -EventFilter.

Invoke-HPECOMServerFirmwareDownload
Stage a firmware bundle on a server without installing it. Supports -Async, -ScheduleTime, and -AllowFirmwareDowngrade.

Invoke-HPECOMGroupServerFirmwareDownload
Stage firmware on all servers in a group. Pipeline input from Get-HPECOMServer -ShowGroupMembership enables subset targeting.

Get-HPECOMServerFirmwareDownloadReport
Retrieve the firmware download status report showing which components are staged and ready for installation.


RENAMED CMDLETS — BACKWARD-COMPATIBLE ALIASES

12 cmdlets renamed; old names kept as aliases — no script changes required.

  Update-HPECOMGroupFirmware                       -> Update-HPECOMGroupServerFirmware
  Stop-HPECOMGroupFirmware                         -> Stop-HPECOMGroupServerFirmware
  Invoke-HPECOMGroupFirmwareComplianceCheck        -> Invoke-HPECOMGroupServerFirmwareComplianceCheck
  Get-HPECOMGroupFirmwareCompliance                -> Get-HPECOMGroupServerFirmwareCompliance
  Invoke-HPECOMGroupInternalStorageConfiguration   -> Invoke-HPECOMGroupServerInternalStorageConfiguration
