ENHANCEMENTS

Get-HPECOMAppliance: new serverCount and groupName output fields; new -ShowAssociatedServers, -ShowCertificate (Secure Gateway only), and -ShowSettings parameters.

Get-HPECOMSetting: 6 new OneView -Category values (ONE_VIEW_APPLIANCE_SOFTWARE, ONE_VIEW_APPLIANCE, ONE_VIEW_SYNERGY_APPLIANCE, ONE_VIEW_SERVER_PROFILE_TEMPLATE, SERVER_FIRMWARE, FIRMWARE_BUNDLE); new -ShowSection for reading specific config sections.

New-HPECOMGroup: -OneViewVMAppliances and -OneViewSynergyAppliances parameters for OVE appliance groups.

Get-HPECOMGroup: -ShowDeviceType filter (DIRECT_CONNECT_SERVER, OVE_APPLIANCE_VM, OVE_APPLIANCE_SYNERGY, OVE_APPLIANCE); -ShowApprovalPolicy to display the attached approval policy.

Case-insensitive name matching: Get-HPECOMGroup, Get-HPECOMApprovalPolicy, Get-HPECOMSetting, Get-HPECOMSchedule, Get-HPECOMWebhook, Get-HPEGLWebhook, Get-HPECOMGroupServerFirmwareCompliance, Get-HPECOMGroupServeriLOConfigurationCompliance.

Wait-HPECOMJobComplete: detects pending approval state and warns rather than timing out silently.

Approvable cmdlets: warns after job submission when job is pending approval, pointing to Get-HPECOMApprovalRequest and Resolve-HPECOMApprovalRequest.

Parameter rename (-ServerSerialNumber/-SerialNumber -> -Name, aliases kept): 16 single-server cmdlets including Start/Stop/Restart-HPECOMServer and Update-HPECOMServerFirmware.

Parameter rename (-ServerSerialNumber -> -ServerName, alias kept): 12 group cmdlets including Update-HPECOMGroupServerFirmware and Invoke-HPECOMGroupServeriLOConfiguration.

Get-HPECOMSchedule: new State column; NextStartAt and -ShowPendingSchedules handle approval-pending schedules correctly.

Get-HPECOMJob: new Resource column; 5 new state filter parameters: -ShowComplete, -ShowApprovalPending, -ShowError, -ShowHalted, -ShowStalled (join existing -ShowRunning, -ShowPending).

Update-HPECOMApplianceFirmware: now non-blocking by default; appliances with jobs in progress are skipped.

Get-HPECOMServer -ShowFibreChannelDetails: retrieve FC HBA port details (WWPNs, speed, boot config) for SAN zoning without an iLO login.

Remove-HPEGLWorkspace -ValidatePrerequisites: check prerequisites before deletion — returns a validation object with blocking resources.

VMware vCenter and Aruba Central added as new external service types via Get/New/Set/Remove-HPECOMExternalService.

New-HPEGLLocation / Set-HPEGLLocation: -Tags, -RemoveTags, and -RemoveAllTags parameters for location tag management.

Set-HPECOMExternalService: DSCC update support via -DSCCRegion; 6 new ServiceNow incident scope parameters.

Connect-HPEGLDeviceComputeiLOtoCOM -Force: force reconnection of an already-connected iLO (supports Direct <-> Secure Gateway migration).

$Global:HPECOMLastJobResult: all job-initiating cmdlets save their last result for post-hoc inspection. Cleared on Disconnect-HPEGL.

Get-HPECOMServer: new -ShowUIDIndicator and -ShowAppliance parameters.

Pipeline input from Get-HPECOMServer -ShowGroupMembership: 12 group job cmdlets now accept it, enabling filtered subset targeting.


BUG FIXES

* New-HPECOMAppliance -OneView: fixed incorrect API endpoint for OneView registration.
* Refresh token expiry now produces a clear message instead of a raw JSON error.
* Get-HPEGLUser: fixed empty table for single-user workspaces.
* Workspace listings no longer include workspaces being deleted.
* Connect-HPEGL: HTML maintenance/outage pages produce a clear error instead of a JSON parse failure.
* COM connection no longer blocks GLP access for users without COM permissions.
* Set-HPECOMExternalService: fixed crash on vCenter certificate retrieval failure; fixed credential validation being silently overwritten.
* Set-HPEGLLocation: fixed validation errors on contact and address update.
* Add/Remove-HPECOMServerToGroup, Invoke-HPECOMGroupServerFirmwareDownload, Get-HPECOMServer: warning messages now correctly display server name.
* Add-HPECOMServerToGroup: fixed incorrect duplicate server detection.
* Get-HPECOMServer -ShowGroupMembership: now returns all servers even before any group has members.
* Get-HPECOMFirmwareBaseline -LatestVersion: now returns exactly one result per generation.
* New-HPECOMSettingServerFirmware: clear error when multiple baselines are accidentally piped in.
* Set-HPECOMSettingServerFirmware: Gen12 baseline no longer silently dropped; existing baselines preserved when not overridden.
* New-HPECOMServerActivationKey: clear error when the 10-key limit is reached.
* Connect-HPEGLDeviceComputeiLOtoCOM: -ResetiLOIfProxyErrorPersists now fires inside the monitoring loop; direct pipeline from Get-HPECOMServer via iLOIPAddress alias.


CODE QUALITY

Pre-validation failures consistently return Warning (not Failed) across all modules. Failed is reserved for actual API errors. Uniform error handling and consistent error details throughout.'

